Label: Descriptor (Main Heading)
Description: A topical term used to describe the subject matter or content of biomedical literature

Label: Qualifier (Subheading)
Description: A term used with descriptors to specify a particular aspect of a subject, such as diagnosis or therapy

Label: Supplementary Concept Record
Description: Terms for specific substances, protocols, or rare diseases added between annual MeSH updates

Label: Topical Descriptor
Description: A descriptor that indicates what a work is about, found in tree categories A through N

Label: Publication Type
Description: A descriptor that indicates the format or genre of a publication rather than its subject

Label: Geographical Descriptor
Description: A descriptor for continents, regions, countries, and other geographic locations

Label: Concept
Description: A specific meaning or idea associated with a MeSH term

Label: Term
Description: A word or phrase used as a name for a concept, including preferred and entry terms

Label: Label
Description: The human-readable name of a MeSH term

Label: Preferred Concept
Description: The main concept representing the intended meaning of a descriptor

Label: Has Concept
Description: Links a descriptor to one of its associated concepts

Label: Has Term
Description: Links a concept to a term used to express it

Label: Preferred Term
Description: The main term used to refer to a concept

Label: Broader Descriptor
Description: A more general term in the MeSH hierarchy

Label: Narrower Descriptor
Description: A more specific term in the MeSH hierarchy

Label: Tree Number
Description: A code indicating the hierarchical position of a descriptor in the MeSH tree

Label: Allowable Qualifier
Description: A subheading that can be used with a particular descriptor

Label: Pharmacological Action
Description: The therapeutic or biological effect of a substance

Label: Scope Note
Description: A definition or explanation of how a MeSH term should be used

Label: Broader
Description: Indicates a more general related concept

Label: Narrower
Description: Indicates a more specific related concept

Label: Anatomy [A]
Description: Descriptors for body structures, organs, tissues, and cells

Label: Organisms [B]
Description: Descriptors for bacteria, viruses, fungi, plants, and animals

Label: Diseases [C]
Description: Descriptors for pathological conditions, syndromes, and signs and symptoms

Label: Chemicals and Drugs [D]
Description: Descriptors for chemical compounds, pharmaceuticals, and biological substances

Label: Analytical, Diagnostic and Therapeutic Techniques and Equipment [E]
Description: Descriptors for medical procedures, diagnostic tests, and treatment methods

Label: Psychiatry and Psychology [F]
Description: Descriptors for mental processes, behavioral sciences, and psychological phenomena

Label: Phenomena and Processes [G]
Description: Descriptors for biological, chemical, and physical processes

Label: Disciplines and Occupations [H]
Description: Descriptors for fields of study, professions, and career specialties

Label: Anthropology, Education, Sociology and Social Phenomena [I]
Description: Descriptors for social sciences and cultural topics

Label: Technology, Industry, Agriculture [J]
Description: Descriptors for industrial processes, agricultural practices, and technology

Label: Humanities [K]
Description: Descriptors for arts, history, religion, and philosophy

Label: Information Science [L]
Description: Descriptors for communication, information management, and computer science

Label: Named Groups [M]
Description: Descriptors for population groups and demographic categories

Label: Health Care [N]
Description: Descriptors for health services, facilities, and healthcare systems

Label: Publication Characteristics [V]
Description: Descriptors for types of publications and document formats

Label: Geographicals [Z]
Description: Descriptors for geographic locations worldwide

Label: Asthma
Description: A chronic respiratory disease characterized by airway inflammation and breathing difficulties

Label: Diabetes Mellitus
Description: A metabolic disorder characterized by high blood sugar levels

Label: Hypertension
Description: A condition of persistently elevated blood pressure

Label: Carcinoma
Description: A malignant tumor arising from epithelial cells

Label: COVID-19
Description: An infectious disease caused by the SARS-CoV-2 virus

Label: Acetaminophen
Description: A pain reliever and fever reducer medication

Label: Anti-Bacterial Agents
Description: Substances that inhibit or kill bacteria

Label: Body Mass Index
Description: A measure of body fat based on height and weight

Label: Magnetic Resonance Imaging
Description: A diagnostic imaging technique using magnetic fields and radio waves

Label: Pregnancy
Description: The state of carrying a developing embryo or fetus

Label: diagnosis
Description: Used for methods and procedures to identify a disease or condition

Label: therapeutic use
Description: Used for substances or procedures employed to treat disease

Label: adverse effects
Description: Used for undesired or harmful effects of treatments or exposures

Label: epidemiology
Description: Used for the distribution and determinants of health conditions in populations

Label: genetics
Description: Used for genetic and hereditary aspects of a condition

Label: prevention & control
Description: Used for methods to prevent or reduce disease occurrence
